text: Alexeyevka () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Alexeyevsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 4,611 as of 2010. There are 34 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Ufa. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Alexeyevka, Ufimsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
